related_questions.question: What is the healthiest potato chip to eat?
related_questions.snippet: In general, the experts recommend avoiding chips made with animal oils as well as coconut, palm or palm kernel oil, which have higher levels of saturated fat. Instead, for the healthiest options, look for chips made with avocado or olive oil, the experts say.
related_questions.title: What are the healthiest chips? Here's what to look for, according to dietitians

related_questions.question: What do British call potato chips?
related_questions.snippet: Fries or Chips or Crisps As ubiquitous in Britain, fried potato slices or wedges are called chips unlike the thin oft-bagged snack in the States — which are crisps in England.
related_questions.title: Crisps

related_questions.question: What is the unhealthiest potato chip?
related_questions.snippet: Potato chips from brands known for excessive salt, saturated fats, and artificial additives tend to be less healthy. Examples include Lay's, Pringles, and Ruffles.
related_questions.title: Which potato chip brands are the most unhealthy? - Quora

related_questions.question: Is eating potato chips healthy?
related_questions.snippet: Dr Chris van Tulleken, an associate professor at University College London and one of the world's most prominent food experts, said that an “enormous number of independent studies clearly link a diet high in ultra-processed foods (like potato chips) to multiple damaging health outcomes including early death”.
